wikipedia_page.main: Fisayo Mubarak Adarabioyo (born 1 February 1995) is an English professional footballer who plays as a striker for Ashton United.

response: | 25 September 2015 || CF ||  || Fisayo Adarabioyo || Macclesfield Town || Free transfer ||

Adarabioyo was born in Manchester, England, to parents of Nigerian lineage and is the youngest of three siblings. His oldest brother, Gbolahan, serves as his representative while Fisayo Adarabioyo is also a footballer who currently plays for Altrincham. All three brothers formerly formed part of Manchester City's youth ranks. After his family moved to Whalley Range when he was still an infant, Adarabioyo was schooled in Manchester and attended Chorlton High School before enrolling with St Bede's College, a college associated with Manchester City.
